Package SuperEasyShare.entities

Class Trip

  • java.lang.Object
    • SuperEasyShare.entities.Trip
  • public class Trip
extends java.lang.Object
    A trip in the car sharing system.
    A trip collects information about time, customer and car involved. It also contains a rate responsible for calculation of the total amount charged for a trip. Some operations' behavior depends on this trip's TripStatus.

    • Field Detail

      • car

        private final Car car
        The car of this trip. Must be non-null.

      • renter

        private final Customer renter
        The customer who rented the car for this trip. Must be non-null. Default is "Unknown".

      • rate

        private final Rate rate
        The rate of this trip, responsible for calculation of the amount charged. Must be non-null. Default is a PerMinuteRate of 1 eurocent/minute.

      • startTime

        private DateTime startTime
        The time when this trip started. Must be in year 2023.

      • endTime

        private DateTime endTime
        The time when this trip ended. Must be after startTime.

      • status

        private TripStatus status
        The state of this trip. Default is CREATED.

      • distance

        private double distance
        The distance traveled. must be >0.

    • Method Detail

      • start

        public Trip start​(DateTime startTime)
        Starts this trip at a specific time.
        Sets start time (if the argument is no tnull) and sets the state to 'started'. This operation is intended for method chaining. Also validates the state of this trip and does not do anythings if this operation cannot be performed on this trip, i.e. neither completed nor started trips can be started.
        Parameters:
        startTime - the time where this trip starts
        Returns:
        this trip

      • end

        public Trip end​(DateTime endTime,
                double distance)
        Ends this trip at a specific time.
        Sets end time (if the argument is valid) and sets the state to 'completed'. This operation is intended for method chaining. Also validates the state of this trip and prints an error message (and leaves this trip unchanged) if this operation cannot be performed on this trip, i.e. only started trips can be * completed.
        Parameters:
        endTime - the time where this trip ends
        distance - the distance traveled
        Returns:
        this trip
